# FIXES: slint-gui-mcp

## Known Limitations

- Capture reliability: `PrintWindow` can fail or return incomplete content for some windows, especially minimized, GPU-accelerated, or non-standard windows.
- Window targeting: partial title matching can hit the wrong window if multiple visible windows share similar titles.
- DPI and scaling: coordinates and screenshot/template alignment can drift on high-DPI or mixed-scaling desktop setups.
- Input strategy: posted mouse and keyboard messages work for many Win32 apps, but not every custom control or security-elevated window will honor them.
- Tool tests: GUI interaction tests depend on a live Windows desktop session with Notepad available; they are not headless-safe.
- Modifier combos: PostMessage-based Ctrl+A/C/V does not work because apps call GetKeyState(). Workaround: dedicated select_all/copy/cut/paste tools using EM_SETSEL and WM_COPY/CUT/PASTE messages.
